Here are the search results for AI SDK React `useChat` documentation regarding `sendMessage` and `parts`:

## Key Findings

### useChat Hook Overview
The useChat API has been significantly updated in AI SDK 5.0. It now uses a transport-based architecture and no longer manages input state internally.

### sendMessage Function
In the Page component, the useChat hook will request to your AI provider endpoint whenever the user sends a message using sendMessage.(no content)The `sendMessage` function is used to send a new message to the chat, which will trigger an API call to generate the assistant response.(no content)You can configure custom body fields on a per-request basis using the second parameter of the sendMessage function. This is useful if you want to pass in additional information to your backend that is not part of the message list.

### Message Parts
